      <head><hi rend="italic">Die Fackel</hi> (The Torch)</head>
      <div>
        <!-- BODY: -->
        <p><hi rend="bold"><hi rend="italic">Die Fackel</hi> (The Torch)</hi>,  satirical Viennese journal published in 922 issues between 1899 and 1936, founded and edited by the Austrian-Jewish writer and journalist Karl Kraus (1874&#x2013;1936).  Schenker evidently read it, because he commented on it in his diaries, and discussed it with others.</p>
        <p>
          <hi rend="italic">Bibliography:</hi>
        </p>
        <p>Edward Timms, <hi rend="italic">Karl Kraus: Apocalyptic Satirist</hi>, 2 vols (New Haven: Yale University Press, 1986, 2005)</p>
